1
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:35,875
DALAH: DEATH AND THE FLOWERS

2
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:51,291
- Be careful, it's hot.
- Yes, of course.

3
00:01:51,375 --> 00:01:53,208
- Go! Quickly.
- Yes, ma'am.

4
00:01:58,583 --> 00:02:01,500
- Hey, Pete, how's the hangover?
- So dizzy.

5
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,208
We've got a family wedding today,

6
00:02:25,291 --> 00:02:30,500
and instead of getting up early to help,
you slept in like always.

7
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:31,708
What kind of in-law are you?

8
00:02:31,791 --> 00:02:36,000
Since you're such an early riser,
what have you helped with this morning?

9
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,583
Oh, wait,
you helped yourself to breakfast.

10
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:46,291
Eldest in-law,
let me give you a little lesson.

11
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:47,958
If your family's up so early,

12
00:02:48,041 --> 00:02:50,625
finish breakfast quickly
and help with preparations

13
00:02:50,708 --> 00:02:52,333
like a good in-law.

14
00:02:52,416 --> 00:02:55,875
Thank you, Jib.
But actually, I did my part last night.

15
00:02:57,041 --> 00:03:00,250
Pa, I've already sorted out
the flower issues.

16
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:04,500
They're using only the big tulips,
and I removed some of the roses.

17
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:06,166
So the numbers match.

18
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:08,083
Mm, thank you.

19
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:15,250
Actually, I crumpled up
some of the roses too.

20
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:18,458
- What's so funny?
- Who does that?

21
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,500
I did that to make sure
our flowers stand out more.

22
00:03:20,583 --> 00:03:23,666
Mm, what a simply amazing effort.

23
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:27,333
Definitely deserving
of the "Best In-Law Award," I'd say.

24
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:30,375
Jib, save that tone
for lecturing your son,

25
00:03:30,916 --> 00:03:33,416
and then maybe
he'll be as good as our daughter,

26
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,625
so there'll be some hope for our family.

27
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:37,833
It's already late, and he's still not up.

28
00:03:39,041 --> 00:03:42,250
- How did you raise him?
- But your sister isn't here either, Sak.

29
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:48,291
Now that we're going to have
a Chinese in-law,

30
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:50,291
we're eating porridge for breakfast.

31
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:53,666
More like Lamduan knows
it's good for a hangover.

32
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:58,291
Well, Mr. Pete and Mr. Sit
threw up a lot last night.

33
00:04:00,041 --> 00:04:03,208
Where were you last night?
You two look like a mess.

34
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:07,291
Well, we went bar-hopping
around Thong Lor.

35
00:04:08,208 --> 00:04:11,333
He dragged me to the first bar,
then we moved to another.

36
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:15,791
When I woke up,
I couldn't remember how many bars.

37
00:04:16,875 --> 00:04:19,166
Listen, drinking is an art form.

38
00:04:20,083 --> 00:04:25,541
So anyway, what do you prefer?
Beer, whiskey, brandy, bourbon, or gin?

39
00:04:26,416 --> 00:04:28,916
You look like… a gin person.

40
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:31,291
You couldn't get enough of gin last night.

41
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:33,500
Stop trying to turn my son
into you, Uncle.

42
00:04:33,583 --> 00:04:35,375
Father would be so damn proud.

43
00:04:35,458 --> 00:04:36,625
Oh, big brother.

44
00:04:37,166 --> 00:04:39,125
I'm not even half of what Ohm is.

45
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:42,666
Uh, Pam, what's wrong?

46
00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:45,416
Pam, what happened to your face?

47
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:47,625
I fell over.

48
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,166
Where? At the floral studio?

49
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,208
You should be more careful.

50
00:04:53,291 --> 00:04:56,458
Lamduan, can you come and treat this cut?

51
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:58,750
Lamduan? Oh!

52
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:01,625
I'll look after it.

53
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:10,416
Hey, has Ohm already gone to the hotel?

54
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,083
I haven't seen him.

55
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:16,041
Why isn't Risa here yet?

56
00:05:16,125 --> 00:05:17,833
It's her wedding today.

57
00:05:19,125 --> 00:05:20,708
Kris either.

58
00:05:20,791 --> 00:05:22,708
Those two do everything together.

59
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,208
Aren't they unusually close?

60
00:05:26,458 --> 00:05:29,125
Risa is Kris's aunt.
Of course they're close.

61
00:05:29,208 --> 00:05:30,791
I think it's more than just close.

62
00:05:31,375 --> 00:05:32,750
That's nonsense.

63
00:05:41,125 --> 00:05:44,291
Great-grandson, it looks good on you.

64
00:05:44,875 --> 00:05:46,416
No need to return it.

65
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:50,708
Great-Grandma, I thank you.

66
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:56,250
So, I heard my name.
What are you talking about?

67
00:05:58,875 --> 00:06:03,041
We were all just wondering
where your aunt is.

68
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:07,833
Oh, she's gone to have her makeup done.
She'll be at the hotel.

69
00:06:07,916 --> 00:06:10,666
Make sure the flash
doesn't wash out my grandson's face.

70
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:16,125
Excuse me.

71
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:20,916
Hello?

72
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:25,750
<i>Kris, why so quiet?</i>

73
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,416
I'm just curious, that's all.

74
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:31,125
No one in the family
seems to know where Risa is,

75
00:06:31,208 --> 00:06:33,208
but you seem to know all her movements.

76
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:36,083
Something going on?

77
00:06:38,208 --> 00:06:39,250
Something wrong, Pop?

78
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:43,541
Even Ohm doesn't seem to know
as much about Risa's story

79
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:44,791
as you do, Kris.

80
00:06:44,875 --> 00:06:46,791
Isn't that strange?

81
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:49,500
Why are you acting weird?
Is something wrong?

82
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:51,833
Can anyone reach Ohm?

83
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:54,083
Dad, what happened?

84
00:06:54,666 --> 00:06:56,333
Anybody know where Risa is?

85
00:06:57,166 --> 00:07:01,041
I'm telling you to be cautious,
in case something happens.

86
00:07:02,041 --> 00:07:03,583
I'm asking you what happened.

87
00:07:04,083 --> 00:07:05,375
The police called.

88
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:09,333
I don't know any more about Aunt Risa
than anyone else here.

89
00:07:10,208 --> 00:07:12,500
I just know
that if it is your wedding day,

90
00:07:12,583 --> 00:07:15,166
you have to get your makeup done
in the morning.

91
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:19,416
Is there anything other than that?

92
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,916
They said…

93
00:07:26,041 --> 00:07:28,875
- What the fuck?
- What did you say? Can't be true.

94
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,833
What the hell?

95
00:07:33,791 --> 00:07:36,541
I was tired
and slept like a log last night.

96
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:38,333
Jae Som's call woke me.

97
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:41,166
She said Mr. Anusorn's body
was found in my studio.

98
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:43,041
What time did she call you?

99
00:07:43,541 --> 00:07:45,416
Um, around 6:00 a.m.

100
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,166
Mm-hmm. Please continue.

101
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:51,166
Then I called Risa,
his bride-to-be,

102
00:07:52,291 --> 00:07:54,291
but I haven't been able to reach her.

103
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,375
- Find her immediately.
- Yes, sir.

104
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:12,750
The family is on the way now
to see the body.

105
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:17,708
What's going on inside?

106
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:22,750
Mr. Ekapop,
care to make a statement?

107
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:26,208
- No press allowed beyond here.
- Mr. Ekapop!

108
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:29,541
Mr. Anusorn was shot in the abdomen.
That was the cause of death.

109
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:31,583
We didn't find any gun at the scene.

110
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:45,625
Wait in the car.

111
00:08:45,708 --> 00:08:50,000
Ohm, my brother! My brother…

112
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:15,875
Who did this?

113
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:19,541
Forensics will need to examine
the scratches on the arm

114
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:23,333
and the cuts on the victim's face.
We're following protocols, sir.

115
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,416
I want a more capable detective.

116
00:09:26,958 --> 00:09:29,958
But this is my jurisdiction, sir.

117
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:31,166
I don't care.

118
00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:00,166
Montree.

119
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:05,166
<i>A shocking and tragic incident</i>
<i>this morning,</i>

120
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:07,416
<i>Dr. Anusorn Uathepa found dead.</i>

121
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:11,625
<i>A candidate for PM,</i>
<i>he was the only son of Mr. Ekapop Uathepa,</i>

122
00:10:11,708 --> 00:10:14,458
<i>former chief of staff</i>
<i>at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</i>

123
00:10:14,541 --> 00:10:17,000
<i>Our reporter is now updating</i>
<i>from the crime scene.</i>

124
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:19,583
- Turn up the volume.
- <i>Good morning, Miss Thapana.</i>

125
00:10:19,666 --> 00:10:22,416
<i>What's the situation</i>
<i>there on the ground as it's unfolding?</i>

126
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:26,333
<i>The police are questioning individuals</i>
<i>involved with the floral studio.</i>

127
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:29,291
<i>- Does not appear to be any clear motive.</i>
- Here's your coffee.

128
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:32,583
- <i>The high-profile wedding…</i>
- Whoa! How was that?

129
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:35,500
What? Huh?

130
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:36,875
Check this out.

131
00:10:36,958 --> 00:10:38,541
Mew, check the news.

132
00:10:38,625 --> 00:10:41,125
<i>Is there any indication whether</i>
<i>the motive is personal…</i>

133
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:42,083
What?

134
00:10:46,083 --> 00:10:48,500
Risa! Risa!

135
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:50,708
Open the door! Are you okay?

136
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:52,791
LEK

137
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:56,625
She's not picking up.

138
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:00,833
Pa. Ohm is dead.

139
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:07,125
WHO KILLED OHM?
IS THAI POLITICS THIS BRUTAL?

140
00:11:07,916 --> 00:11:08,958
PITY. STILL YOUNG AND HOT

141
00:11:13,625 --> 00:11:15,666
<i>The body is undergoing</i>
<i>an autopsy.</i>

142
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:19,041
<i>There is still no statement</i>
<i>from the For Thai Society Party,</i>

143
00:11:19,125 --> 00:11:23,250
<i>but this is expected to have a huge impact</i>
<i>on their election campaign.</i>

144
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:29,625
<i>We must now wait</i>
<i>for the police to investigate.</i>

145
00:11:29,708 --> 00:11:30,958
Party's next move?

146
00:11:31,041 --> 00:11:33,250
- There's nothing decided yet.
- New candidate?

147
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:36,916
- We do not have any clear answers.
- Opinion on this incident?

148
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,875
As a representative of a competing party,

149
00:11:39,958 --> 00:11:44,125
I extend our condolences
to the Uathepa family…

150
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:46,416
<i>…for the loss of Anusorn Uathepa</i>

151
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,166
<i>in this tragic homicide.</i>

152
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,375
The family has no comment.

153
00:11:50,458 --> 00:11:52,750
<i>…a young man</i>
<i>who displayed immense potential.</i>

154
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:53,666
MORNING NEWS

155
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:55,291
<i>The whole nation is completely shocked.</i>

156
00:11:55,375 --> 00:11:59,083
<i>Dr. Anusorn Uathepa was a beacon of hope</i>
<i>to the young generation.</i>

157
00:11:59,166 --> 00:12:01,166
<i>His campaign attracted immense interest.</i>

158
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:03,208
<i>The image of hope</i>
<i>is one thing,</i>

159
00:12:03,291 --> 00:12:05,458
<i>but let's not forget that Dr. Anusorn</i>

160
00:12:05,541 --> 00:12:08,666
<i>was also instrumental in planning</i>
<i>the new community mall at--</i>

161
00:12:15,791 --> 00:12:17,958
Is our business affected by this?

162
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,208
Pong?

163
00:12:20,875 --> 00:12:22,458
Uh… uh…

164
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,125
I don't think so, Pa.

165
00:12:25,666 --> 00:12:28,333
We've already received their land
as part of the dowry.

166
00:12:29,125 --> 00:12:32,458
It's even better for us now
that we don't have to care at all

167
00:12:32,541 --> 00:12:33,750
about his politics.

168
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:36,333
We can now ignore the protest

169
00:12:36,416 --> 00:12:38,541
and turn the Square into a mall
as planned.

170
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:40,416
Yes, you're right. Good.

171
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:45,875
Uh, I can help handle the donations
for Ohm's funeral expenses.

172
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:50,125
Only senior family members handle finance.

173
00:12:50,875 --> 00:12:52,166
Yes, that's right.

174
00:12:53,125 --> 00:12:54,958
I will talk to them myself.

175
00:12:55,958 --> 00:12:58,916
Well, has anyone found out where Risa is?

176
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,958
Uh, Kris has gone to find her.

177
00:13:02,041 --> 00:13:03,291
No need to worry, Pa.

178
00:13:03,375 --> 00:13:04,833
All the more reason to worry.

179
00:13:17,083 --> 00:13:18,416
She's still inside?

180
00:13:19,625 --> 00:13:22,083
Yes, it's been hours. Her phone's off too.

181
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:25,583
Here.

182
00:13:29,541 --> 00:13:30,375
Noomnim?

183
00:13:30,458 --> 00:13:31,375
Risa?

184
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:33,125
Risa, it's me.

185
00:13:38,708 --> 00:13:41,833
There's no need to worry.
Miss Risa just wants to be alone.

186
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,041
Still a little girl.

187
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:05,583
- Hello, sir.
- Do you have anything to say?

188
00:14:05,666 --> 00:14:07,333
Can you give us a statement?

189
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:09,666
- Anything to say?
- Good morning. This way, sir.

190
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:12,166
- Can you answer questions?
- Updates?

191
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:13,916
Excuse us.

192
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,416
- Sir? Sir?
- Can you make a statement?

193
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:18,666
Can we at least get a photo?

194
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:23,833
This way, sir.
She's waiting inside for you.

195
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:36,458
Good morning, sir.

196
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:44,500
Miss Dalah Rose.

197
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:54,458
Did you hear anything
particularly unusual last night?

198
00:14:54,541 --> 00:14:57,416
I heard an electrical transformer explode.

199
00:14:58,708 --> 00:15:00,166
Then I went to bed.

200
00:15:02,916 --> 00:15:04,833
So nobody heard a gunshot?

201
00:15:06,416 --> 00:15:08,416
There were fireworks going all night.

202
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:10,750
I see.

203
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:13,916
Jae Som,
when did you call Dalah about the body?

204
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:15,583
Around six.

205
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:20,416
You were at the studio last night, yes?

206
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:23,125
That's right,
but I was the first to leave.

207
00:15:23,208 --> 00:15:26,166
The bride and groom were still there
when I left,

208
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:28,125
and also a girl.

209
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:30,708
I think she was a cousin
or something like that.

210
00:15:30,791 --> 00:15:31,625
Pam.

211
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:35,666
Are you familiar with Pam?

212
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,750
I'm the one asking questions here.

213
00:15:40,625 --> 00:15:43,291
They came to check out the flowers,

214
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:45,625
because we had some problems
with the tulips.

215
00:15:47,625 --> 00:15:49,083
Why was Pam there?

216
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:51,541
I was just tagging along.

217
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:56,458
I talked to Uncle Ohm about his campaign,
and I wanted to discuss it again.

218
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,041
How did you get that-- that scratch?

219
00:16:01,125 --> 00:16:04,666
I tripped running to my girlfriend's car.
I didn't want to keep her waiting.

220
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:08,541
Why didn't you go home with your Uncle Ohm
or Risa, since you came with them?

221
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:13,500
I'd looked at the flowers,
and I'd spoken to Uncle Ohm.

222
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:17,000
- The adults were so boring.
- Still, you didn't need to call her.

223
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:22,000
Okay. I'll tell you the truth.

224
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:26,666
My girlfriend was itching for it.

225
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,000
Itching?

226
00:16:32,791 --> 00:16:33,750
PAM'S FOOTPRINT

227
00:16:37,708 --> 00:16:40,250
Pam left at around 10:30 p.m.

228
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:45,458
That's the time Mr. Ekapop and Mrs. Prapha
approved my floral design.

229
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:47,916
Then they left as well.

230
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,958
Why did Mrs. Prapha come,
and not Mr. Kitja?

231
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:54,833
You think Pa wanted to check himself?

232
00:16:54,916 --> 00:16:57,250
That's why he has a dependable in-law
like me.

233
00:16:57,833 --> 00:16:59,375
I'm the eldest.

234
00:16:59,458 --> 00:17:01,666
It's natural
that I look after his interests.

235
00:17:02,666 --> 00:17:03,791
How did you get there?

236
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:08,416
I drove my wife there,
and then I waited in the car.

237
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:10,833
- Any witnesses?
- I came out to see off Mrs. Prapha.

238
00:17:10,916 --> 00:17:12,291
See you tomorrow.

239
00:17:12,375 --> 00:17:13,291
See you.

240
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:15,458
<i>I didn't see anyone in the car.</i>

241
00:17:17,041 --> 00:17:19,125
<i>I was napping</i>
<i>on the reclining seat.</i>

242
00:17:19,208 --> 00:17:20,375
<i>That's why no one saw me.</i>

243
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,166
But I did see Kris.

244
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,666
Mr. Kris was also there.

