00:32:32,875 --> 00:32:34,208
It was probably too late.

485
00:32:35,250 --> 00:32:37,458
What is it that you're saying?

486
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:40,708
Grandma…

487
00:32:42,125 --> 00:32:44,625
I'm sorry
for having to tell you the truth.

488
00:32:45,291 --> 00:32:48,583
I alerted you before about taking Jib in.

489
00:32:49,250 --> 00:32:52,125
She doesn't raise her kids well.
She's all Thai.

490
00:32:52,208 --> 00:32:55,541
What's wrong with that?
What's so fucking wrong with it?

491
00:32:56,250 --> 00:32:59,083
I can't believe
you agree with her, Grandma.

492
00:33:01,875 --> 00:33:03,875
I'm going to bed.

493
00:33:05,666 --> 00:33:07,375
What did you say to Grandma?

494
00:33:08,083 --> 00:33:09,416
I just told her the truth.

495
00:33:09,500 --> 00:33:10,458
What truth?

496
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:14,083
If you don't want the police
to know about this scandal,

497
00:33:14,166 --> 00:33:17,916
you better tell your father what it is
that his favorite grandson has done.

498
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:19,291
What?

499
00:33:19,375 --> 00:33:22,833
You know what I'm talking about!

500
00:33:22,916 --> 00:33:24,916
And I'm telling you,
I won't let you have everything

501
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,416
just because you have a son.

502
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:29,500
You think you're entitled
with a lousy son like that

503
00:33:29,583 --> 00:33:32,666
