529
00:37:43,875 --> 00:37:45,291
- Hey!
- Yes?

530
00:37:45,375 --> 00:37:46,750
Go home and rest now.

531
00:37:47,333 --> 00:37:50,125
Big day tomorrow, and the press.

532
00:37:50,916 --> 00:37:51,750
Okay.

533
00:37:55,208 --> 00:37:57,041
Finally, you called me.

534
00:37:57,125 --> 00:37:59,416
<i>Dr. Anusorn Uathepa found dead.</i>

535
00:37:59,500 --> 00:38:03,333
<i>A candidate for PM, he was the only son</i>
<i>of Mr. Ekapop Uathepa…</i>

536
00:38:03,416 --> 00:38:05,333
<i>What about Noomnim and Kris?</i>

537
00:38:05,416 --> 00:38:07,958
<i>No worries.</i>
<i>They were very convincing.</i>

538
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:15,291
<i>Not just me.</i>

539
00:38:15,375 --> 00:38:18,500
<i>When you came with the police,</i>
<i>your acting was pretty good too.</i>

540
00:38:18,583 --> 00:38:19,583
<i>No.</i>

541
00:38:21,750 --> 00:38:23,000
I wasn't acting.

542
00:38:29,208 --> 00:38:31,791
- You're naturally deadpan, right?
- Here you go.

543
00:38:36,708 --> 00:38:37,541
Let me help.

544
00:39:26,833 --> 00:39:29,666
<i>When blossoms</i>
<i>reach their peak in bloom,</i>

545
00:39:31,250 --> 00:39:34,541
<i>some exude a pungent fume.</i>

546
00:39:35,125 --> 00:39:38,083
<i>Yet we tend to value them by their looks.</i>

547
00:39:39,791 --> 00:39:42,625
<i>When flowers start to droop and wither…</i>

548
00:39:44,625 --> 00:39:48,125
<i>unleashing a scent that chokes us bitter.</i>

549
00:39:48,208 --> 00:39:51,208
<i>As if they sought their silent vengeance…</i>

550
00:39:53,500 --> 00:39:56,708
